[{"id":"FT571075","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p>The situation depicted in the image best serves as evidence of the</p>","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p><strong>Question refers to the excerpt below.</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left: 120px;\"><strong>Alfred R. Waud, “The Freedmen’s Bureau,” 1868</strong></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"The figure presents a drawing with the caption “Alfred R. Waud, ‘The Freedmen’s Bureau,’ 1868.” In the drawing, a solider in the uniform of the Union army is standing between two groups of people who appear to be hostile toward each other. He is facing the group on the left, which is made up of White men. The group on the right is made up of Black men. He is holding a hand up to the group of White men and a hand down to the group of Black men. Both groups of men are holding weapons. A United States flag is prominently displayed, hanging from a building directly behind the soldier.\" height=\"283\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/f784b807e65b90b748ac12c2baa29e14/original.jpg\" width=\"425\" /></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:0.8em\">Courtesy of the Library of Congress #LC-USZ62-105555</span></p>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p> expansion of federal power</p>","<p> decline of an agrarian economy</p>","<p> increase in sectional divisions</p>","<p> institutionalization of racial segregation</p>"],"answer":-1}]